The paper discusses memory-augmented neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on optimizing memory utilization, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses computer vision tasks, which fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses neural networks, which fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses optimization, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
